The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Mohun Bagan decide to give IFA Shield a miss
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Mohun Bagan decide to give IFA Shield a miss
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Federation Cup champions Mohun Bagan have decided not to participate in the ensuing IFA Shield scheduled to begin from January 4.         
	Club officials after a meeting on Monday evening told reporters about their decision to skip the century old tournament. The club had decided to rest the players keeping in mind the second phase of the I-League, starting January 15.         
	We are not playing in the IFA Shield, Bagan secretary Anjan Mitra said on Monday evening.         
	According to the official, the players  after playing back-to-back tournaments starting from the Premier Division, I-League and the Federation Cup  were a tried lot.         
	They (players) are also human beings. They have played back-to-back tournaments starting from the Premier Division We cannot force them to play the IFA Shield, he added.         
	We think its high time for them to take some rest and come back fresh for the second leg of the I-League, the secretary said.         
	Asked whether Bagan would send their under-19 squad for the tournament, he said: Whenever Mohun Bagan play a tournament they give their best and play to win it So there is no question of sending the juniors for the meet We are not thinking about it We have sent a letter to the IFA about our decision.         
	Asked whether the club will bow to IFAs pressure to play in the tournament, he said: Most of our players have been granted two weeks rest and they will be leaving for their home tomorrow So we will have no players to play         
	It was learnt that Bagans outstation players will leave for home on Tuesday and will rejoin practice on January 5, a day after the scheduled start to the IFA Shield.         
	IFA secretary Utpal Ganguli when contacted said: We have received a letter from Mohun Bagan We will sit with them (Bagan officials) and talk it out within the next couple of days.                                                                                                                          
